      "daily_reflection": "So for breakfast today, I had, post egg on toast at home. This is something I have quite regularly because, I like eggs, good protein, and toast. And it's quick, quick, and easy to make, and it's very cheap. And it keeps me full for most of the day. And then, for lunch, I had quite a late lunch because I was out during the day. And I needed to eat something before I went out this evening because I was knew I was going out at a certain time so I knew I was gonna be hungry before then. So I had a chicken steak and some mixed Spanish grains which was really nice and really quick to make, really easy, really cheap, not too much food. It was, something I'd make if I'm in a rush generally. I had a similar meal the other day. And then for tea, I went out with my friends because I'm haven't seen them for a while. And the restaurant that we went to has a fifty percent off offer at the moment on main meals, so it was cheaper than usual. So we thought we'd take this opportunity to go out for food. And I had, pork and mash and sauce and some mixed vegetables. And then we had a dessert as well because, the food was discounted. So we felt that it was good value for money to get a dessert as well because it would still be relatively cheap."
